(412379, 'Chu', 'arrested at a protest at the Capitol', 'Rep. Chu was arrested in a protest at the Capitol on June 30, 2022. The House Committee on Ethics [released a report indicating she will pay the $50 fine](https://ethics.house.gov/sites/ethics.house.gov/files/documents/Committee%20Report_41.pdf).', '- date: 2022-07-22', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(408094, 'Myers', 'conspiracy to deprive voters of civil rights, bribery, obstruction of justice, falsification of voting records, and conspiring to vote illegally in a federal election', 'Pleaded guilty.', '- date: 2022-06-08', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456793, 'Jacobs', 'failure to report stock trades', 'In 2022, the House Committee on Ethics published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Jacobs''s response to allegations he failed to report stock trades in accordance with the STOCK Act. In July of 2022, the Committee unanimously voted to dismiss the referral.', '- date: 2022-05-31', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456833, 'Cawthorn', 'participating in a investment "pump and dump" scheme', 'Cawthorn lost his primary.', '- date: 2022-04-23', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456845, 'Fallon', 'failing to disclose stock trades in the required time', 'In 2022, the House Committee on Ethics announced it had extended the matter regarding [allegations that the representative had failed to disclose stock trades in the required time](https://www.forbes.com/sites/zacheverson/2022/04/20/house-ethics-committee-is-investigating-texas-republican-pat-fallon/?sh=21ea49f21c65). In May 2022, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Fallon''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-pat-0). In July of 2022, the Committee unanimously voted to dismiss the referral.', '- date: 2022-03-02', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412692, 'Rutherford', 'failure to report stock trades', 'In 2022, the House Committee on Ethics announced an investigation into the representative. In May 2022, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Rutherford''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-66). It appears that the allegation relates to a [failure to report stock trades in 2021](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-66). In August of 2022, the Committee unanimously voted to dismiss the referral.', '- date: 2022-02-28', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412717, 'Suozzi', 'failing to disclose stock transactions', 'In 2022, the House Committee on Ethics announced it would extend its investigation of allegations of [failing to disclose stock transactions](https://buffalonews.com/news/house-ethics-committee-extends-probe-of-suozzi-stock-trades/article_86899d28-bcca-11ec-b3ed-6f0957a47be0.html). In July of 2022, the Committee unanimously voted to dismiss the referral.', '- date: 2022-02-28', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456847, 'Jackson', 'campaign finance violations', 'Jackson''s office said that the investigation concerned alleged campaign finance violations.', '- date: 2021-12-22', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456833, 'Cawthorn', 'driving on a revoked license as well as speeding', 'Cawthorn lost his primary.', '- date: 2022-03-09', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412791, 'Omar', 'ommitting required financial disclosures and accepting an advance on her memoir', 'In 2021, Rep. Omar was accused of ommitting required financial disclosures and accepting an advance on her memoir. The Office of Congressional Ethics [voted unanimously in December 2021 to recommend that the House Committee on Ethics dismiss the case](https://ethics.house.gov/sites/ethics.house.gov/files/documents/OCE%20Report_5.pdf) for lack of evidence. In 2022, two of the four House Committee on Ethics members did not vote to dismiss, but House rules have no guidelines for how to proceed in this situation so [no further action will be taken](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-ilhan).', '- date: 2021-12-17', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456805, 'Boebert', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'Rep. Boebert was fined for failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic.', '- date: 2022-03-21', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412574, 'Weber', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'In 2021, Rep. Weber was fined for failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic.', '- date: 2021-11-30', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456839, 'Bowman', 'protesting at the Capitol', 'In January 2022, Rep. Bowman was arrested while protesting at the Capitol. He informed the Committee he will pay the $200 fine and no further action will be taken by the Committee.', '- date: 2022-04-02', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412552, 'Meadows', 'being in criminal contempt of Congress', 'In December 2021, the [House of Representatives voted 220-208 to hold former Rep. Meadows in criminal contempt of Congress](https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/117-2021/h447) for refusing to comply with a subpoena to appear before the January 6 Committee, but the Department of Justice [declined to prosecute](https://edition.cnn.com/2022/06/03/politics/justice-department-declines-charge-meadows-scavino-january-6/index.html).', '- date: 2021-12-14', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456817, 'Miller-Meeks', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'In 2021, Rep. Meeks was [fined for failing to wear a mask on the House floor](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-49) during the COVID-19 pandemic.', '- date: 2021-11-30', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456819, 'Newman', 'promising a Congressional staff position to someone if they did not run against her in the 2020 primary', 'In 2021, Rep. Newman was accused of [promising a staff position to a potential opponent](https://chicago.suntimes.com/columnists/2021/12/12/22831391/rep-marie-newman-democratic-primary-rep-sean-casten-faces-political-damage-ethics-probe) if he agreed not to run against her in the 2020 primary. In January of 2022, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Newman''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-54). In 2023, the Committee [reported that the end of the member''s term ended the committee''s jurisdiction](https://www.congress.gov/117/crpt/hrpt706/CRPT-117hrpt706.pdf#page=+35).', '- date: 2021-10-25', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412191, 'Lamborn', 'engaging in a wide variety of abusive behaviors towards Congressional staff', 'In 2021, Rep. Lamborn was sued for a [wide variety of abusive behaviors towards Congressional staff](https://www.rollcall.com/2021/05/14/doug-lamborn-likely-to-face-house-ethics-scrutiny/). In January 2022, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Lamborn''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-53). The Committee [carried its investigation into the 118th Congress](https://www.congress.gov/117/crpt/hrpt706/CRPT-117hrpt706.pdf#page=+33).', '- date: 2021-10-25', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456853, 'Good', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'In 2021, Rep. Good was fined for failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic. The Rep. appealed his fine, but [the appeal was denied](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-bob).', '- date: 2021-09-27', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412777, 'Baird', 'failing to complete security screening to enter House Floor', 'Baird appealed fine.', '- date: 2021-11-17', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412397, 'Gosar', 'posting a video clip altered with official Congressional resources to make it look like he killed his colleague, Rep. Ocasio-Cortez, and flew at President Biden with swords via his official social media accounts', 'Rep. Gosar posted the video clip.', '- date: 2021-11-07', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456813, 'Clyde', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'Since 2021, Rep. Clyde was fined many times for failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic. The Rep. appealed his fines several times, but all have been denied. With a $500 fine for the first time and a $2,500 fine for each subsequent time, it is believed that, as of June 2022, Clyde has been fined at least $103,000, taken out of his congressional salary.', '- date: 2021-09-21', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456814, 'Greene', 'repeatedly failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'Greene appealed the fine.', '- date: 2021-05-20', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412820, 'Crenshaw', 'failing to complete security screening to enter House Floor', 'In October 2021, the Committee agreed to Rep. Crenshaw''s appeal of a fine for failing to complete security screening to enter House Floor.', '- date: 2021-10-25', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400640, 'Fortenberry', 'scheming to falsify and conceal material facts and making false statements to federal investigators', 'Fortenberry announced he would resign effective March 31, 2022.', '- date: 2021-10-19', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412826, 'Roy', 'failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic', 'In the summer of 2021, Rep. Roy was fined for failing to wear a mask on the House floor during the COVID-19 pandemic.', '- date: 2021-08-02', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
