(412722, 'Smucker', 'failure to complete security screening on May 19', 'Rep. Smucker [failed to complete security screening on May 19, 2021 and was fined $5,000](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-lloyd). Smucker appealed and on June 28, 2021, the Committee [rejected his appeal](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-27).', '- date: 2021-05-24', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400643, 'Foxx', 'failure to complete security screening on May 13', 'Rep. Foxx [failed to complete security screening on May 13, 2021 and was fined $5,000](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-24).', '- date: 2020-05-18', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400075, 'Clyburn', 'failing to complete security screening on April 20, 2021', 'Rep. Clyburn was accused of [failing to complete security screening on April 20, 2021](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-james) but on May 20, the House Committee on Ethics [agreed to Clyburn''s appeal](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-25).', '- date: 2021-04-23', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400340, 'Rogers', 'failing to complete security screening on April 14, 2021', 'Rep. Rogers was accused of [failing to complete security screening on April 14, 2021](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-hal). On May 20, the House Committee on Ethics [agreed to Roger''s appeal](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-hal-0).', '- date: 2021-04-20', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412393, 'Tom Reed', 'engaging in sexual misconduct', 'Reed resigned.', '- date: 2021-04-09', 'r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(412690, 'Gaetz', 'engaging in a sexual relationship with underage girl, using illicit drugs, sharing inappropriate images or videos on the House floor, misusing state identification records, converting campaign funds to personal use, and accepting a bribe, improper gratuity, or impermissible gift', 'The New York Times reported that the Department of Justice was investigating Rep. Matt Gaetz over allegedly engaging in a sexual relationship with an underage girl.', '- date: 2021-03-30', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , c, r, i, m, e,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400651, 'Gohmert', 'failing to complete security screening on February 4, 2021', 'Rep. Gohmert [failed to complete security screening on February 4, 2021 and was fined $5,000](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-louis). He appealed on February 26 and the appeal was denied by the committee on March 30, 2021.', '- date: 2021-03-11', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456813, 'Clyde', 'failing to complete security screening on February 3, 2021', 'Rep. Clyde [failed to complete security screening on February 3, 2021 and was fined $5,000](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-20). On April 12, the [Committee rejected Clyde''s appeals](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-23).', '- date: 2021-03-11', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412773, 'Fulcher', 'assaulting a Capitol Police officer when refusing to fully comply with security procedures before entering the House floor on January 12, 2021', 'Rep. Fulcher was accused of assaulting a Capitol Police officer when [refusing to fully comply with security procedures before entering the House floor on January 12, 2021](https://www.huffpost.com/entry/capitol-police-investigate-member-incidents-metal-detectors-house-chamber_n_602dd485c5b67c32961b2d8e?aod). That the Capitol Police were investigating became public when they interviewed a Huffington Post reporter who''d witnessed the event as part of the investigation. Soon after, the U.S. Capitol Police sent a letter to Fulcher saying [there was no investigation at that time](https://www.kivitv.com/news/capitol-police-rep-fulcher-not-under-investigation).', '- date: 2021-02-17', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412434, 'Harris', 'attempting to carry a concealed firearm onto the House floor on January 21, 2021', 'Rep. Harris was accused of [attempting to carry a concealed firearm onto the House floor on January 21, 2021](https://www.huffpost.com/entry/house-congressman-gun-andy-harris_n_600a0874c5b674575ae423ae?gjl). That [the Capitol Police were investigating](https://www.huffpost.com/entry/capitol-police-investigate-member-incidents-metal-detectors-house-chamber_n_602dd485c5b67c32961b2d8e?aod) became public when they interviewed a Huffington Post reporter who''d witnessed the event as part of the investigation.', '- date: 2021-02-17', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400344, 'Ros-Lehtinen', 'using campaign funds for personal expenses', 'The Department of Justice closed the investigation without charges.', '- date: 2020-09-25', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412779, 'Watkins', 'interfering with law enforcement by providing false information, voting without being qualified and unlawful advance voting', 'Watkins lost in the Kansas Republican primary.', '- date: 2020-07-14', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(456790, 'Loeffler', 'trading stock based on learning non-public information in committee meetings', 'At some point between March 2020 when news broke that stocks owned by Sen. Loeffler were sold right after a committee briefing on the possible trajectory of covid19 and June 17, 2020, the Senate Ethics Committee opened an investigation into the trades. On June 17, they [sent a letter](https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/senate-ethics-panel-dismisses-probe-into-sen-loeffler-for-insider-trading/2020/06/16/f8ca3196-b01e-11ea-8f56-63f38c990077_story.html) to Sen. Loeffler informing her than since the Department of Justice had ended its investigation, they would too. No record of the investigation or the letter are available publicly.', '- date: 2020-06-17', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400030, 'Bishop', 'spending Members� Representational Allowance (MRA) funds on holiday events in his district and converting campaign funds to personal use', 'Rep. Bishop was investigated for spending both House office funds and campaign funds for personal use, including on annual holiday gatherings and tuition. The investigation [has been carried into the 118th Congress](https://www.congress.gov/117/crpt/hrpt706/CRPT-117hrpt706.pdf#page=+28).', '- date: 2020-06-16', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400054, 'Burr', 'covid19 stock profiteering', 'Sen. Burr stepped down as chair of the Senate Intelligence Committee.', '- date: 2020-03-17', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412781, 'Trahan', 'accepting excessive campaign contributions and failing to file required disclosure documents', 'In September 2019, Trahan was accused of accepting excessive campaign contributions and failing to file required disclosure documents. In December 2019, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Trahan''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-8). In July 2020, the House Committee on Ethics [published its report dismissing the charges](https://ethics.house.gov/sites/ethics.house.gov/files/documents/Committee%20Report_17.pdf) since the alleged excessive contributions were part of joint holdings with her spouse and any reporting errors were unintentional.', '- date: 2019-08-18', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412787, 'Tlaib', 'reporting improper campaign expenditures', 'In 2019, Tlaib was accused of reporting improper campaign expenditures. In August, the Office of Congressional Ethics [recommended further review](https://oce.house.gov/reports/investigations/oce-referral-regarding-rep-rashida-tlaib) by the House Committee on Ethics. In November, the House Committee on Ethics [published the Office of Congressional Ethics Report and Findings and Tlaib''s response](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-5). In August 2020, the House Committee on Ethics found that while Rep. Tlaib did receive campaign funds for personal use after the 2018 general election, it was an error and not malfeasance. She is fined $10,800, the amount she received after the election.', '- date: 2019-08-16', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412765, 'Spano', 'receiving improper and excessive loans for his election campaign', 'In 2019, Spano was accused of receiving improper and excessive loans for his election campaign. In August, the Office of Congressional Ethics [recommended further review](https://oce.house.gov/reports/investigations/oce-report-regarding-rep-ross-spano) by the House Committee on Ethics. In November, the House Committee on Ethics [deferred its investigation to the Department of Justice](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-4). Spano lost his election in 2020 and the Committee [reported that the end of the member''s term ended the committee''s jurisdiction](https://www.congress.gov/116/crpt/hrpt703/CRPT-116hrpt703.pdf#page=+33).', '- date: 2019-08-16', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412437, 'Huizenga', 'accepting campaign contributions from staff and making improper campaign expenditures', 'In 2019, Huizenga was accused of accepting campaign contributions from staff and making improper campaign expenditures. In August that year, the Office of Congressional Ethics [recommended further review](https://oce.house.gov/reports/investigations/oce-referral-regarding-rep-bill-huizenga) by the House Committee on Ethics. In 2024, the Committee [closed the matter](https://ethics.house.gov/sites/ethics.house.gov/files/documents/Committee%20Report_58.pdf) saying "Based on the totality of the circumstances, including the lack of any clear pattern of misspending or intentional circumvention of any standards of conduct, as well as Representative Huizenga�s consistent cooperation with this review, the significant remedial steps that his campaign has undertaken, and the widespread need for updated guidance on the personal use of campaign funds, the Committee determined that Representative Huizenga�s conduct did not merit a sanction."', '- date: 2019-08-16', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400170, 'Hastings', 'engaging in improper relationship with a staff member and receiving improper gifts and/or forebearance from the staff member', 'In 2019, Hastings was alleged to have engaged in improper relationship with a staff member and received improper gifts and/or forebearance from the staff member. The House Committee on Ethics began an investigation. In 2020, the House Committee on Ethics [closed the investigation](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-10) since the employee was his spouse, gifts from family are acceptable and their employment did not violate any House rules when they were hired.', '- date: 2019-11-04', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(412770, 'San Nicolas', 'engaging in a sexual relationship with a staff member, converting campaign funds to personal use and/or accepting improper or excessive campaign contributions', 'In 2019, San Nicolas was alleged to have engaged in a sexual relationship with a staff member, converted campaign funds to personal use and/or accepted improper or excessive campaign contributions. In 2020, the House Committee on Ethics[established an Investigative Subcommittee](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-delegate-michael-f-0) to further investigate the allegations following a referral from the Office of Congressional Ethics. In 2022, the Investigative Subcommittee found that there was at least some evidence for all the allegations, but the most significant evidence was for the financial allegations. In light of Del. San Nicolas''s planned retirement at the end of this Congress, [the Committee has referred its report to the Department of Justice](https://ethics.house.gov/press-releases/statement-chairman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-delegate-michael-1).', '- date: 2019-10-24', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(412756, 'Hill', 'having a sexual relationship with office staffer', 'Resigned from Congress.', '- date: 2019-10-23', 'r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(400162, 'Grijalva', 'the representative created a hostile work environment and was frequently drunk', 'At an unspecified date during Rep. Grijalva''s service in Congress, he was accused of creating a hostile work environment and being frequently drunk. The claims, always denied by Grijalva, were resolved with a severance payment in 2015 although none of this became public until 2017. According to news reports, Grijalva was cleared by the House Ethics Committee [letter](https://rollcall.com/2018/12/19/house-ethics-clears-rep-raul-grijalva-of-wrongdoing/) in Dec 2018. Now, his case is apparently [being reviewed by the House Committee on Ethics](https://www.azcentral.com/story/news/politics/arizona/2019/06/14/rep-raul-grijalva-under-scrutiny-house-ethics-committee-over-workplace-allegations/1460308001/), although what for and why is unknown.', '- date: 2018-05-15', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , u, n, r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412690, 'Gaetz', 'violating the Florida Supreme Court''s rules for attornies by attempting to intimidate a witness scheduled to testify before the House Judiciary Committee.', 'Gaetz refused to appear for an interview with the committee.', '- date: 2019-02-27', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400172, 'Hayes', 'bribery and conspiracy to commit honest services wire fraud, along with several counts of making false statements', 'Pardoned by President Trump.', '- date: 2019-04-02', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412627, 'Blum', 'omitting required information from financial disclosure reports; permitting the use of official House resources for a private business in which he had a financial interest and the use of unfair or deceptive trade practices', 'Blum lost the election. - date: 2018-12-17', '- date: 2018-07-19', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412729, 'Garrett', 'using Congressional staff to perform unofficial work and personal errands', 'Garrett announced he is an alcoholic and would not run for re-election.', '- date: 2018-05-28', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
