(412730, 'Jayapal', 'crowding, obstructing, or incommoding, during a protest inside a Senate Office Building in Washington, D.C.', 'On June 28, Rep. Jayapal was arrested for crowding, obstructing, or incommoding, during a protest inside a Senate Office Building in Washington, D.C. The House Committee on Ethics concluded that [no further investigation was needed](https://www.congress.gov/115/crpt/hrpt876/CRPT-115hrpt876.pdf) since Rep. Jayapal had paid a $50 fine and charges were dropped.', '- date: 2018-06-25', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412399, 'Schweikert', 'using or authorizing impermissable expenditures from Representative Schweikert�s Members� Representational Allowance and receiving improper campaign contributions; failure to provide financial disclosure information', 'In 2018, Rep. Schweikert was accused of using or authorizing impermissable expenditures from his Members� Representational Allowance and receiving improper campaign contributions. In June 2018, the House Committee on Ethics [established an Investigative Subcommittee (ISC)](https://ethics.house.gov/press-release/statement-chairwoman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-19). In December of 2018, the ISC [expanded its investigation](https://ethics.house.gov/press-release/statement-chairwoman-and-ranking-member-committee-ethics-regarding-representative-28) and added alleged failure to make financial disclosures. On July 30, 2020, the House Committee on Ethics published their report, [concluded he was guilty of all charges](https://www.congress.gov/congressional-report/116th-congress/house-report/465), recommended a reprimand and fined Schweikert $50,000. On July 31, 2020, the [House voted unanimously](https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/house-votes-to-reprimand-gop-rep-schweikert-for-11-ethics-violations/2020/07/31/2490303e-d327-11ea-9038-af089b63ac21_story.html) in a voice vote to formally reprimand Rep. Schweikert.', '- date: 2018-06-28', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
