(412487, 'McKinley', 'remaining a named partner in his prior business after being elected to Congress', 'In 2016 McKinley received a letter of reproval for remaining a named partner in his prior business after being elected to Congress. The House Committee on Ethics concluded that McKinley violated House rules and [issued a letter of reproval](https://www.congress.gov/114/crpt/hrpt795/CRPT-114hrpt795.pdf).', '- date: 2016-09-27', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412552, 'Meadows', 'retaining an employee through 2015 who did not perform duties after 2014 commensurate with the compensation the employee received', 'In 2016 Meadows was investigated for retaining an employee through 2015 who did not perform duties after 2014 commensurate with the compensation the employee received. This employee, Mr. West, had been demoted after Meadows learned of West''s sexual harassment of other Meadows'' staff. Meadows commissioned his own investigation and ignored the recommendation to fire West. Further, Meadows did not seek guidance on whether continuing to pay West was in accordance with House Rules and his separatist approach to keeping West on staff, but away from women staff was effectively discriminatory since it precluded their access to to Meadows. For these reasons, the Committee [unanimously voted to reprove Meadows and to require him to repay West''s excess two month''s salary of $40,625.02](https://ethics.house.gov/sites/ethics.house.gov/files/Meadows%20Report%20FINAL%20with%20sigs.pdf).', '- date: 2016-05-18', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(400431, 'Whitfield', 'permitting his spouse to lobby him and/or his congressional staff from 2011 to 2014', 'In 2016 Whitfield received a letter of reproval for permitting his spouse to lobby him and/or his congressional staff from 2011 to 2014. The House Committee on Ethics found the violation occured and that [the report would be the reproval](https://www.congress.gov/114/crpt/hrpt687/CRPT-114hrpt687.pdf).', '- date: 2014-11-10', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412196, 'Buchanan', 'improperly influencing a witness before the FEC and illegally reimbursing campaign contributors', 'In 2012 Buchanan was investigated for improperly influencing a witness before the FEC and illegally reimbursing campaign contributors. The House Committee on Ethics concluded that there was insufficient evidence on the allegation of witness tampering, but that [the illegal reimbursements did occur, albeit without the representative''s knowledge](https://www.congress.gov/114/crpt/hrpt643/CRPT-114hrpt643.pdf).', '- date: 2012-05-09', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
