(404587, 'Gingrich', 'improper use of official resources in preparation of a college course, conflict of interest, and improper use of tax-exempt entities in support of college course; investigation expanded to 1) false statements to committee on Standards, 2) relationship with foundation/course in violation of foundation�s tax-exempt status under Section 501(c)3 of the IRS Code, 3) use of unofficial resources for official purposes, and 4) activities and relationship with another foundation', 'On Jan. 17, 1997, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gingrich for improper use of official resources in preparation of a college course, conflict of interest, and improper use of tax-exempt entities in support of college course. The investigation was expanded to 1) false statements to the Committee on Standards, 2) his relationship with the foundation/course in violation of foundation�s tax-exempt status under Section 501(c)3 of the IRS Code, 3) his use of unofficial resources for official purposes, and 4) his activities and relationship with another foundation. The committee investigated and dismissed the first two allegations (Gingrich made restitution to pay for the use of the official resources). On Jan. 21, 1997, the House of Representatives [reprimanded Gingrich and directed him to reimburse $300,000, 395-28](https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/105-1997/h8).', '- date: 1997-01-17', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(402762, 'Collins', 'misuse official resources, campaign resources and scholarship funds', 'Defeated in the primary. - date: 1997-01-02', '- date: 1996-08-06', 'e, l, e, c, t, i, o, n, s,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400146, 'Gephardt', 'inadequate financial disclosure on a series of land sales and financial agreements regarding property purchased and exchanged in North Carolina', 'On Sep. 28, 1997, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gephardt for inadequate financial disclosure on a series of land sales and financial agreements regarding property purchased and exchanged in North Carolina. The committee [dismissed the complaint](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf#page=+28).', '- date: 1997-09-28', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400262, 'McDermott', 'conflict of interest (participated in committee deliberations involving complaints filed with the substantial assistance of a - person affiliated with his political action committee) and violation of committee confidentiality rules', 'On Jul. 24, 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated McDermott for conflict of interest (he participated in committee deliberations involving complaints filed with the substantial assistance of a person affiliated with his political action committee) and violation of committee confidentiality rules. The committee [dismissed the complaint](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf#page=+30).', '- date: 1996-07-24', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gringrich', 'improper use of services of volunteer in congressional office', 'In 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gringrich for improper use of services of volunteer in congressional office via a complaint known as the Third Miller Complaint. The [charges were dismissed](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf#page=+21) on Sep. 19, 1996.', '- date: 1996-09-19', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(410147, 'Solomon', 'retaliation for political disagreement', 'In 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Solomon for a press release and letter sent to a New York state assemblyman which included language that implied possible retaliation for political disagreement. On May. 8, 1996, the [complaint was dismissed](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf#page=+29) after Solomon indicated he had not retaliated and had never intended to retaliate.', '- date: 1996-05-08', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400527, 'Bonior', 'improper use of congressional employees with regard to book published by Bonior in 1984 and improper salary payments to member of staff prior to her marriage to him', 'On May. 9, 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Bonior for improper use of congressional employees with regard to a book published by Bonior in 1984 and improper salary payments to member of staff prior to her marriage to him. On May. 8, 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct [dismissed the second complaint](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf#page=+29). On May. 9, 1996, the committee returned the first complaint because the alleged violations occurred before the third previous Congress.', '- date: 1996-05-08', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gingrich', 'improper use of services of volunteer in congressional offices', 'On Mar. 29, 1996, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gingrich for the improper use of the services of a volunteer in congressional offices and [concluded that the volunteer service, which had terminated by the time of the complaint, did not comply with the applicable guidelines](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt886/CRPT-104hrpt886.pdf).', '- date: 1996-03-29', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(300156, 'Torricelli', 'using congressional fax machine to send a press release having a political purpose (accusation made by Rep. Thomas)', 'Zimmer lost his bid for a New Jersey Senate seat to Torricelli.', '- date: 1996-03-29', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(412001, 'Zimmer', 'using congressional fax machine for non-official purpose, specifically to send a press release entitled "Zimmer Wallops Torricelli in N.J. Congressional Softball Tourney" which was a personal attack and therefore violated usage rules (accusation made by Torricelli)', 'Zimmer lost his bid for a New Jersey Senate seat to Torricelli.', '- date: 1996-03-29', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400597, 'McIntosh', 'distributing at a committee meeting and displaying on House floor a document attributed to an outside group that was instead created by representative''s staff and allowing subcommittee staff to improperly question a witness regarding their observance of a religious holiday', 'McIntosh apologized and formalized a written policy for his staff regarding harassing, insensitive or discriminatory behavior.', '- date: 1996-03-14', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(410974, 'Tucker', 'seven counts of extortion and two counts of tax evasion for extorting $30,000 from a local businessman while he was mayor of Compton, CA and failing to report payments on his taxes, for which he was convicted on December 8, 1995', 'Announced resignation effective Dec. 15, 1995.', '- date: 1995-12-12', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gingrich', 'improper statements on House floor for political reasons; official resources used for political purposes', 'In 1995, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gingrich for improper statements on House floor for political reasons and using official resource for political purposes. The complaints were [dismissed](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt401/CRPT-104hrpt401.pdf) in a public letter on Dec. 6, 1995 and a public report issued on Dec. 12, 1995.', '- date: 1995-12-12', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gingrich', 'accepting free cable television coverage of college lectures (improper gifts/solicitation)', 'In 1995, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gingrich for accepting free cable television coverage of college lectures  as improper gifts/solicitation. The complaint was [dismissed](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt401/CRPT-104hrpt401.pdf) in a public letter on Dec. 6, 1995 and a public report issued on Dec. 12, 1995.', '- date: 1995-12-12', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gingrich', 'improperly using services of volunteer for official purposes', 'In 1995, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gingrich for improperly using the services of a volunteer for official purposes in a complaint known as the First Miller Complaint. The committee found violations and sent a public letter to Gingrich and took no further action on Dec. 6, 1995. The committee [published its report](https://www.congress.gov/104/crpt/hrpt401/CRPT-104hrpt401.pdf) on Dec. 12, 1995.', '- date: 1995-12-12', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
