(404598, 'Glenn', 'improperly intervening on behalf of Charles Keating, Jr. and his savings and loan business', 'In 1989, Sen. Glenn was accused of improperly intervening with federal banking regulators on behalf of Charles Keating, Jr. and his savings and loan business. In 1991, the Senate Select Committee on Ethics published a report in which charges were dismissed.', '- date: 1991-11-20', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(300071, 'McCain', 'improperly intervening on behalf of Charles Keating, Jr. and his savings and loan business', 'In 1989, Sen. McCain was accused of improperly intervening with federal banking regulators on behalf of Charles Keating, Jr. and his savings and loan business. In 1991, the Senate Select Committee on Ethics published a report in which charges were dismissed even though they did indicate that McCain had demonstrated poor judgement in attending a meeting with federal regulators on Keating''s behalf. McCain remained in the Senate until his death in 2018. In the intervening years, he [testified against Keating (the only one of the five to do so)](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Keating_Five#Aftermath) in a civil trial and became an [advocate of campaign finance reform](https://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/article/2018/aug/31/sen-john-mccain-fought-clean-money-politics-are-we/).', '- date: 1991-11-20', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(406995, 'Lukens', 'contributing to the unruliness of a female minor, e.g. sex with an underage girl on May 26, 1989, for which he was convicted as a misdemeanor; improper sexual advances to Capitol elevator operator on Oct. 17, 1990', 'Resigned.', '- date: 1990-10-24', 'r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d,  , s, e, x, u, a, l, -, h, a, r, a, s, s, m, e, n, t, -, a, b, u, s, e'),
(403669, 'Durenberger', 'a wide range of financial misconduct', 'Durenberger faced an allegation of a wide range of financial misconduct. On Jul. 25, 1990, the Senate [voted to denounce him 96-0, which appears to have been intended as a type of censure which acknowledges no ill intent](https://www.senate.gov/about/powers-procedures/censure/141DavidDurenberger.htm).', '- date: 1990-07-25', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(410574, 'Swindall', 'money laundering and lying to the FBI', 'Started serving a one year prison sentence in a minimum-security federal prison after remaining free on bond while his appeals were active.', '- date: 1989', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(400140, 'Frank', '1) use of personal residence for prostitution by third parties, 2) improper contacts with probation office on behalf of personal assistant, 3) improper dismissal of assistant�s parking tickets, and 4) sexual activity in the House gymnasium', 'Preliminary inquiry voted (Sept. 12, 1989); Frank admitted preparing memo containing misleading statements that could be perceived as an attempt to use political influence in a judicial matter and arranged improper dismissal of parking tickets for personal assistant, both in violation of R. 43 (1); committee recommended reprimand and restitution of parking tickets, 12-0 (July 20, 1990).', '- date: 1990-07-20', 'c, r, i, m, e,  , e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(404587, 'Gringrich', 'using book partnership to avoid outside income limits or to obtain impermissible gifts or contributions, improper use of official resources to prepare book, and inadequate financial disclosure', 'In 1990, the House Committee on Standards of Official Conduct investigated Gringrich for using book partnership to avoid outside income limits or to obtain impermissible gifts or contributions, improper use of official resources to prepare book, and inadequate financial disclosure. The committee issued a statement on Mar. 8, 1990.', '- date: 1990-03-08', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
