(410325, 'Stephenson', 'electoral misconduct, bribery, and corruption', 'Stephenson faced an allegation of electoral misconduct, bribery, and corruption. On Jun. 11, 1911, the Committee on Privileges and Elections issued a majority report recommending he retain his seat and the minority report disagreeing. On Mar. 12, 1912, the Senate [voted to allow him to keep his seate 40-34](https://hdl.handle.net/2027/umn.31951p00933065r?urlappend=%3Bseq=319).', '- date: 1911-06-11', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
(406935, 'Lorimer', 'electoral misconduct, bribery, and corruption of a state legislature in order to secure election to the Senate', 'Lorimer committed electoral misconduct, bribery, and corruption of a state legislature in order to secure election to the Senate (this was immediately before the 17th Amendement passed providing for direct election of senators). On Mar. 1, 1911, the Senate vote to unseat him failed 40-46. But on Jul. 13, 1912, the [Senate unseated him by a vote of 55-28](https://www.govtrack.us/congress/votes/62-2/s204).', '- date: 1910-06-01', 'c, o, r, r, u, p, t, i, o, n,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
