(410118, 'Smoot', 'Mormonism', 'Smoot faced an allegation of Mormonism, which was indeed his religion. On Jun. 2, 1906, the Committee on Privileges and Elections recommended expulsion 7-5 solely because he was a Mormon. On Feb. 20, 1907, the Senate [first decided to require a 2/3 majority for expulsion which failed 27-43, and second to unseat him, which also failed 28-42](https://hdl.handle.net/2027/umn.31951p00933065r?urlappend=%3Bseq=306).', '- date: 1906-06-02', 'e, t, h, i, c, s,  , r, e, s, o, l, v, e, d'),
